{{see|Ancien Régime}}

==French==
===Etymology===
French ''Ancient Régime'', ''Old Rule'', ''Old Order''; the word first appeared in English in print in 1794.

===Noun===
'''ancien régime''' (''plural:'' '''[[anciens régimes]]''')

# {{cattag|pejorative connotation}} A system of government long since supplanted by another, particularly a state of [[feudalism]] with an absolute monarchy supported by the doctrine of the [[Divine Right of Kings]].

